<h3>21 October 2025 - Appeal Window Dispute</h3>

 

<div class="quote-box">

  <div class="quote-header">Email: Appeal Deadline (Incorrect Calculation by Employer)</div>

  <div class="quote-label">Reference: E0-APPEAL-EXPIRED-001 | Date: 21/10/2025</div>

  

  <div class="quote-label">Verbatim Text (Original)</div>

  <div class="quote-verbatim">

    "The timeframe for submitting a formal appeal expired on 20 October 2025 at 23:59."

  </div>

 

  <div class="quote-metadata">

    <strong>Date/Time:</strong> <span class="timestamp">21/10/2025</span>

    <br/>

    <strong>Calculation Error:</strong> Employer asserts deadline of 20/10 23:59. Dismissal letter states "within 5 working days OF RECEIVING this letter". Claimant received letter 16/10. 5 working days from 16/10 = 23/10/2025. Employer's calculation (from 13/10 send date) is incorrect - "of receiving" means from receipt date, not send date. Claimant's appeal notice filed 17/10 (within correct deadline).

    <br/>

    <strong>Legal Significance:</strong> ACAS Code §4 breach (frustration of genuine right of appeal); Procedural unfairness (s.98(4) ERA); Misinterpretation of contractual term; Bad faith (employer counts from send date, not receipt).

  </div>

</div>

 

