    <br/>

    <strong>Context:</strong> Post-dismissal, employer sends formal letter threatening: (1) Deduction from final wages of disputed equipment values. (2) If total exceeds certain threshold, pursue civil claim (Small Claims Court). (3) 24-hour return ultimatum. Final payment document (04/11) shows NO deduction actually applied. Therefore, threat was made but not executed.

    <br/>

    <strong>Legal Significance:</strong> ERA s.13 (unlawful deduction threat - even if not executed, threat is a violation); Coercion; Post-termination harassment (EqA s.26); Breach of mutual trust and confidence.

  </div>

</div>

 

<h2>A1.4 Legal Analysis (ERA s.13 &amp; s.23)</h2>

 

<p>

  <strong>ERA 1996 s.13 - Unlawful Deductions:</strong> An employer shall not make deductions from wages unless:

</p>

 

<ol>

  <li>Authorised by written contract, OR</li>

  <li>Authorised by statute, OR</li>

  <li>Agreed in writing by the employee.</li>

</ol>

 

<p>

  <strong>Application to this case:</strong>

</p>

 

<ul>

  <li><strong>No contractual clause:</strong> Employment contract (CP-01) contains NO clause authorising deduction for equipment loss/damage.</li>

  <li><strong>No statutory authority:</strong> No statute authorises employer to deduct equipment values from wages.</li>

  <li><strong>No written agreement:</strong> Claimant did NOT agree to deduction. Employer unilaterally "declared" values and threatened deduction.</li>

</ul>

 

<p>

  <strong>Conclusion:</strong> Any deduction attempted (or threatened) violates ERA s.13 and ERA s.23 (restriction on contracting out of rights).

</p>

 

<h2>A1.5 Relief Sought (A1)</h2>

 

<ol>

  <li><strong>Confirmation:</strong> All wages due for 1-13 October 2025 were lawfully paid in accordance with contract (no unlawful deduction made).</li>

  <li><strong>Declaration:</strong> Any post-dismissal threat to deduct equipment values is unlawful under ERA s.13.</li>

  <li><strong>Injunction (interim):</strong> Employer is prohibited from making any such deduction from future payments, pension, or benefits.</li>

  <li><strong>Statutory interest:</strong> On any established underpayment, at 8% per annum from the date of underpayment (from 13/10/2025).</li>

  <li><strong>Costs &amp; expenses:</strong> Legal and tribunal fees incurred in defence of unlawful deduction threat.</li>

</ol>

 

<p style="border-left: 2pt solid #0b3f5c; padding: 8pt 10pt; margin: 8pt 0pt; font-size: 10pt; widows: 3; orphans: 3;">

  <strong>Note for A10 (Global Schedule):</strong> Section A1 establishes that final payment was lawful (no deduction applied). However, the threat itself is actionable under ERA s.13 (unlawful deduction threat) and contributes to harassment/coercion under EqA s.26 and breach of mutual trust and confidence. Impact on damages will be assessed in context of full fact pattern (A1-A12).

</p>

 

<p style="page-break-after: always; margin: 0pt; padding: 0pt;">

  &nbsp;

</p>

 

