<h2>A2.6 Relief Sought (A2)</h2>

 

<ol>

  <li><strong>Declaration:</strong> Claimant was required to perform additional hours (40-70 per month) beyond 196-hour benchmark.</li>

  <li><strong>Payment:</strong> Undocumented additional hours to be paid at implied hourly rate (GBP 17.09/hour gross).</li>

  <li><strong>Award range:</strong> Conservative GBP 5,144 to Full GBP 8,994.</li>

  <li><strong>Statutory interest:</strong> 8% per annum from each month worked (Feb-Oct 2025).</li>

  <li><strong>Alternative:</strong> If hours cannot be precisely quantified, award a reasonable lump sum (GBP 6,500) based on scope creep evidence.</li>

</ol>

 

<p style="page-break-after: always; margin: 0pt; padding: 0pt;">

  &nbsp;

</p>

 

<!-- ========== SEKCJA A3 ========== -->

 

<h1>A3: Procedural Fairness &amp; ACAS Code Breaches</h1>

 

<h2>A3.1 Six Core ACAS Code Breaches</h2>

 

<table>

  <thead>

    <tr>

      <th>Breach</th>

      <th>ACAS §</th>

      <th>What Happened</th>

      <th>Why Unreasonable</th>

      <th>Consequential to Unfairness?</th>

    </tr>

  </thead>

  <tbody>

    <tr>

      <td><strong>1. Short notice</strong></td>

      <td>§12-14</td>

      <td>&lt;24 hours notice</td>

      <td>Manifestly insufficient; ACAS standard = 48h minimum</td>

      <td>YES - No time for evidence prep</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td><strong>2. No pre-disclosure</strong></td>

      <td>§2</td>

      <td>Evidence "at hearing" only</td>

      <td>Fundamental right denied to prepare defence</td>

      <td>YES - Can't address allegations</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td><strong>3. Biased chair</strong></td>

      <td>§6</td>

      <td>Lukasz (involved in dispute) conducts; Przemek (spouse/co-owner) present</td>

      <td>No separation of roles; perception of bias</td>

      <td>YES - Can't believe in impartiality</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td><strong>4. Health ignored</strong></td>

      <td>§10-15</td>

      <td>Fit note disregarded; no adjustment offered</td>

      <td>Employer has duty to consider health; no effort to do so</td>

      <td>YES - Discriminatory; unfair</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td><strong>5. 66-minute hearing</strong></td>

      <td>§6-9</td>

      <td>From 13:00 to 14:06 (1 hour 6 min)</td>

      <td>Grossly inadequate for 3+ allegations; predetermination evident</td>

      <td>YES - Indicates rushed/unjust</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td><strong>6. Appeal deadline miscounted</strong></td>

      <td>§4</td>

      <td>Counted from send (13/10), not receipt (16/10)</td>

      <td>Contract says "within 5 working days of receiving"; employer ignores "receiving"</td>

      <td>YES - Frustrates appeal right</td>

    </tr>

  </tbody>

</table>

 

