<h2>A4.3 Failure to Make Reasonable Adjustments (s.20-21 EqA)</h2>

 

<p>

  <strong>Reasonable Adjustments Required But NOT Offered:</strong>

</p>

 

<table>

  <thead>

    <tr>

      <th>Adjustment</th>

      <th>Why Required</th>

      <th>Status</th>

      <th>Legal Impact</th>

    </tr>

  </thead>

  <tbody>

    <tr>

      <td>Postponement to post-fit-note period</td>

      <td>Claimant unfit for work (fit note: 13/10-14/11)</td>

      <td>NOT OFFERED - Employer refused</td>

      <td>Breach s.20-21 EqA</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td>Remote attendance / written submission</td>

      <td>Allow participation without requiring attendance</td>

      <td>NOT OFFERED - Employer refused</td>

      <td>Breach s.20-21 EqA</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td>48+ hours notice (ACAS standard)</td>

      <td>ADHD individuals need processing time</td>

      <td>NOT PROVIDED - &lt;24 hours given</td>

      <td>Breach s.20-21 EqA; ACAS Code §12-14</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td>Pre-disclosure of evidence</td>

      <td>Allow preparation; manage anxiety</td>

      <td>NOT PROVIDED - "at hearing itself"</td>

      <td>Breach s.20-21 EqA; ACAS Code §2</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td>Support person / representation</td>

      <td>Stress-related disability support</td>

      <td>NOT OFFERED</td>

      <td>Breach s.20-21 EqA</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td>Impartial chair</td>

      <td>Ensure fairness; reduce stress</td>

      <td>NOT PROVIDED - Lukasz was party to dispute</td>

      <td>Breach s.20-21 EqA; ACAS Code §6</td>

    </tr>

  </tbody>

</table>

 

<h2>A4.4 S.15 EqA - Discrimination Arising from Disability</h2>

 

<p>

  <strong>Elements of s.15 Claim:</strong>

</p>

 

<ol>

  <li><strong>Disability:</strong> ADHD (confirmed diagnosis; stress manifestation)</li>

  <li><strong>Unfavourable treatment:</strong> Dismissal without fair process; no adjustments</li>

  <li><strong>Because of something arising from disability:</strong> Stress (stress-related unfitness is manifestation of ADHD)</li>

  <li><strong>Objective justification:</strong> Employer could have postponed; no justification for refusing adjustment</li>

</ol>

 

<p>

  <strong>Application:</strong> Claimant had stress-related unfitness (arising from ADHD disability). Employer dismissed without offering any reasonable adjustment. No objective justification exists for refusing postponement. Therefore, dismissal breaches s.15 EqA.

</p>

 

<h2>A4.5 Relief Sought (A4)</h2>

 

<ol>

  <li><strong>Declaration:</strong> Claimant has ADHD disability under EqA 2010 s.6.</li>

  <li><strong>Declaration:</strong> Employer failed to make reasonable adjustments (s.20-21 EqA).</li>

  <li><strong>Declaration:</strong> Dismissal discriminated based on disability (s.15 EqA).</li>

  <li><strong>Compensation:</strong> Separate Vento award for injury to feelings (discrimination head).</li>

  <li><strong>Statutory interest:</strong> 8% per annum from date of dismissal (13/10/2025).</li>

</ol>

 

<hr class="page-break"/>

 

