<h2>A7.5 Justification for 12-18 Month Award Period</h2>

 

<ol>

  <li><strong>Automatic unfairness (s.104 ERA):</strong> Under s.104, no "contributory conduct" reduction applies. Full period justified.</li>

  <li><strong>Disability discrimination (EqA):</strong> ADHD individual requires longer recovery from workplace trauma; job-seeking delayed due to health impact.</li>

  <li><strong>Reputational damage:</strong> Dismissal for "misconduct" (unauthorised absence) circulates in industry; affects hirability.</li>

  <li><strong>Age &amp; seniority:</strong> 39-year-old senior manager (GM) has narrower market for similar roles than junior staff.</li>

  <li><strong>Medical fitness:</strong> Fit note extends to 14 Dec 2025; active job-seeking unlikely before January 2026. Realistic re-employment period ~mid-April 2026.</li>

  <li><strong>Cumulative injustice:</strong> Harassment (9 months), unfair dismissal (multiple breaches), disability discrimination, post-dismissal intimidation - all increase appropriate award period.</li>

</ol>

 

