<h1>A9: ACAS Code Uplift (s.207A TULRCA 1992)</h1>

 

<h2>A9.1 Legal Framework</h2>

 

<p>

  <strong>s.207A TULRCA 1992:</strong> If a tribunal finds that a party has unreasonably failed to comply with the ACAS Code of Practice on Disciplinary and Grievance Procedures, the tribunal may increase the award by up to 25%.

</p>

 

<h2>A9.2 Application Criteria</h2>

 

<ol>

  <li><strong>Unreasonable failure to comply:</strong> Not technical breach; must be unreasonable</li>

  <li><strong>Consequential to complaint being well-founded:</strong> Breach must have contributed to dismissal being unfair (or discrimination occurring)</li>

  <li><strong>Proportionality:</strong> Uplift (0-25%) reflects severity of breach</li>

</ol>

 

<h2>A9.3 Six Documented ACAS Code Breaches</h2>

 

<table>

  <thead>

    <tr>

      <th>Breach #</th>

      <th>ACAS §</th>

      <th>What Employer Did</th>

      <th>Unreasonable?</th>

      <th>Consequential?</th>

    </tr>

  </thead>

  <tbody>

    <tr>

      <td>1</td>

      <td>§12-14</td>

      <td>&lt;24 hours notice (Sunday to Monday)</td>

      <td>YES - Manifestly inadequate</td>

      <td>YES - Claimant couldn't prepare</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td>2</td>

      <td>§2</td>

      <td>No pre-disclosure of evidence</td>

      <td>YES - Fundamental right denied</td>

      <td>YES - Can't address allegations</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td>3</td>

      <td>§6</td>

      <td>Biased chair (Lukasz involved; Przemek co-owner)</td>

      <td>YES - No separation of roles</td>

      <td>YES - Can't believe in fairness</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td>4</td>

      <td>§10-15</td>

      <td>Fit note disregarded; no adjustment</td>

      <td>YES - Duty to consider health ignored</td>

      <td>YES - Discriminatory; unfair</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td>5</td>

      <td>§6-9</td>

      <td>66-minute hearing for 3+ allegations</td>

      <td>YES - Grossly inadequate</td>

      <td>YES - Predetermination evident</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td>6</td>

      <td>§4</td>

      <td>Appeal deadline miscalculated</td>

      <td>YES - Frustrates appeal right</td>

      <td>YES - Prevents genuine appeal process</td>

    </tr>

  </tbody>

</table>

 

<h2>A9.4 Calculation of Uplift (25%)</h2>

 

<p>

  <strong>Rationale for 25% (Maximum):</strong>

</p>

 

<ul>

  <li><strong>Six distinct ACAS Code breaches:</strong> Not one or two peripheral breaches; six core, separate violations</li>
  <li><strong>All unreasonable:</strong> Each breach, individually, is unreasonable; cumulatively, egregious</li>

  <li><strong>All consequential:</strong> Each breach prevented fair hearing and contributed to unfairness finding</li>

  <li><strong>Pattern of deliberateness:</strong> Not accidental slips; systematic violations (rushed hearing, no disclosure, biased chair, health ignored)</li>

  <li><strong>Bad faith indicators:</strong> Predetermination messages; financial motive; misrepresentation of law</li>

  <li><strong>No genuine attempt at compliance:</strong> When objections raised (12/10 by Claimant), employer dismissed concerns and proceeded</li>

</ul>

 

<p>

  <strong>Under s.207A guidance, 25% uplift is justified because:</strong>

</p>

 

<ol>

  <li>Multiple unreasonable failures (not single technical breach)</li>

  <li>Failures were causative of unfairness (all contributed to dismissal being unfair)</li>

  <li>Employer's conduct warrants maximum penalty within statutory range</li>

</ol>

 

<h2>A9.5 Uplift Calculation (Example: 12-Month Loss Scenario)</h2>

 

<table>

  <thead>

    <tr>

      <th>Component</th>

      <th>Amount (GBP)</th>

    </tr>

  </thead>

  <tbody>

    <tr>

      <td>Compensatory award (unfair dismissal, net)</td>

      <td>26,035</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td>ACAS uplift 25%</td>

      <td>6,509</td>

    </tr>

    <tr>

      <td style="background: #ffffff;"><strong>Subtotal (with uplift)</strong></td>

      <td style="background: #ffffff;"><strong>32,544</strong></td>

    </tr>

  </tbody>

</table>

 

<p>

  <strong>Note:</strong> Uplift applies to compensatory award only (unfair dismissal). It does NOT apply to discrimination awards (EqA) or harassment awards (s.26 EqA), which are separate heads.

</p>

 

