<h1>Conclusion</h1>

 

<p>

  This claim presents a strong, well-documented case across multiple legal heads:

</p>

 

<ol>

  <li><strong>Unfair Dismissal:</strong> Reason not genuine (moving goalposts; misstatement of law); Procedure massively unfair (6 ACAS breaches); Financial motive evident (cost-cutting); Predetermination manifest (trust messages before hearing).</li>

 

  <li><strong>Disability Discrimination:</strong> ADHD diagnosis confirmed (July 2025 psychiatric assessment); Employer knew of health issue (GP referral October); Fit note issued same day as hearing; No adjustments offered despite mandatory duty under s.20-21 EqA.</li>

 

  <li><strong>Harassment:</strong> 9-month pattern documented (vulgarity, dehumanization, isolation); Public humiliation (WhatsApp announcement); Post-dismissal intimidation (legal threats, equipment demands); Cumulative effect destroys dignity.</li>

 

  <li><strong>Unlawful Deduction &amp; Additional Hours:</strong> Equipment deduction threatened without contractual basis (ERA s.13 breach); Additional hours (40-70/month) worked but undocumented (time-logging prohibited); ERA s.13 breach for both threats and underpayment.</li>

 

  <li><strong>Breach of Contract:</strong> Implied term of mutual trust and confidence fundamentally breached through sustained pattern of disrespect, coercion, and bad faith.</li>

</ol>

 

<p>

  <strong>Strengths of Claim:</strong>

</p>

 

<ul>

  <li>Comprehensive documentary evidence (60+ exhibits: emails, chats, payslips, medical records)</li>

  <li>Contemporaneous records (most evidence from emails/WhatsApp sent at time of conduct)</li>

  <li>Objective procedural violations (ACAS Code breaches not matters of discretion)</li>

  <li>Medical evidence (ADHD diagnosis; fit notes)</li>

  <li>Financial motive clearly documented (cash-flow crisis disclosure 10 days before dismissal)</li>

  <li>Predetermination signals (trust messages before formal hearing)</li>

  <li>Misstatement of law on record (s.57A false assertion)</li>

  <li>Multiple legal heads (unfair dismissal AND discrimination AND harassment = cumulative liability)</li>

</ul>

 

<p>

  <strong>Estimated Tribunal Award Range: GBP 76,688 - GBP 137,935</strong>

  <br/>

  <strong>Most Likely Range (Mid-Scenario): GBP 98,644 - GBP 125,000</strong>

</p>

 

